<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12004k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12004k">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12004k"> 4(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pay in fat to find smarriti</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> quand on avait perdu quelque chose, il suffisait d&apos;aller &agrave; leur demeure et de crier: &ldquo; Poulpiquet, j&apos;ai &eacute;gar&eacute; tel objet&rdquo;, pour &ecirc;tre s&ucirc;r de trouver &agrave; sa porte, quelques heures apr&egrave;s, ce qu&apos;on avait perdu. Pour leur r&eacute;compense, ils n&apos;&eacute;taient pas exigeants, ils ne demandaient qu&apos;un peu de graisse pour leur soupe ou leur bouillie, car, &mdash; c&apos;est leur principal d&eacute;faut, &mdash; ils sont tr&egrave;s gourmands. <br><font color="green">[&hellip; <mark>when one lost something</mark>, it was enough to go to their dwelling and cry &ldquo;Poulpiquet, I have mislaid such an object&rdquo; to be sure to find at one&apos;s door, several hours later, the thing one had lost. In return (they were not demanding) <mark>they only asked for a little fat</mark> for their soup or their gruel since &mdash; and this is their main flaw &mdash; they are very greedy.]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 12</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: It. <i>Smarriti</i>: lost objects. </mm> </dd></dl>
